    <h1><i class="fas fa-spell-check"></i> Spell Check</h1>
    <p class="help-intro">Check spelling across all text inputs in the application.</p>
    
    <div class="help-block">
        <h2>What is Spell Check?</h2>
        <p>
            Spell check automatically highlights misspelled words as you type in any text field. 
            This helps maintain professional, error-free documentation in your financial records.
        </p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="help-block">
        <h2>How to Use Spell Check</h2>
        
        <h3>Basic Usage:</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Start typing in any text field (description, notes, payee name, etc.)</li>
            <li>Misspelled words will show a red wavy underline</li>
            <li>Right-click on the underlined word</li>
            <li>Choose the correct spelling from suggestions, or select "Add to Dictionary"</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
    
    <div class="help-block">
        <h2>Settings</h2>
        <p>Customize spell check behavior in <strong>Settings</strong> ? <strong>Spell Check</strong>:</p>
        
        <table class="help-table">
            <tr>
                <td><strong>Enable spell checking</strong></td>
                <td>Turn spell check on or off globally</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td><strong>Use browser spell check</strong></td>
                <td>Use your browser's native spell checker (recommended)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td><strong>Check as you type</strong></td>
                <td>Check spelling while typing vs only when submitting forms</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td><strong>Underline errors</strong></td>
                <td>Show wavy underline on misspelled words</td>
            </tr>
        </table>
    </div>
    
    <div class="help-block">
        <h2>Custom Dictionary</h2>
        <p>The app includes a custom dictionary with nonprofit and finance-specific terms that won't be marked as errors:</p>
        
        <div class="help-example">
            <h4>Included Terms:</h4>
            <div class="custom-dictionary-list">
                <span class="custom-dictionary-word">nonprofit</span>
                <span class="custom-dictionary-word">fundraising</span>
                <span class="custom-dictionary-word">grantor</span>
                <span class="custom-dictionary-word">grantee</span>
                <span class="custom-dictionary-word">payee</span>
                <span class="custom-dictionary-word">reimbursement</span>
                <span class="custom-dictionary-word">AFG</span>
                <span class="custom-dictionary-word">FEMA</span>
                <span class="custom-dictionary-word">SAFER</span>
                <span class="custom-dictionary-word">SCBA</span>
                <span class="custom-dictionary-word">501c3</span>
                <span class="custom-dictionary-word">unrestricted</span>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-2"><small>...and more! Over 25 terms included.</small></p>
        </div>
        
        <h3>Adding Your Own Words:</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Right-click on a word marked as misspelled</li>
            <li>Select "Add to Dictionary"</li>
            <li>The word will be remembered for future use</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
    
    <div class="help-block">
        <h2>Where Spell Check Works</h2>
        <p>Spell check is active in:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Transaction descriptions</strong> - Keep financial records professional</li>
            <li><strong>Notes fields</strong> - Document details accurately</li>
            <li><strong>Donor/Grant descriptions</strong> - Maintain professional correspondence</li>
            <li><strong>Category names</strong> - Clear, correct categorization</li>
            <li><strong>Comments and memos</strong> - Professional internal documentation</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3>Where Spell Check Doesn't Apply:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Password fields (for security)</li>
            <li>Email addresses</li>
            <li>Numbers and amounts</li>
            <li>Phone numbers</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div class="help-block">
        <h2>Benefits</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Professional Reports</strong> - No spelling errors in Form 990 or board reports</li>
            <li><strong>Grant Applications</strong> - Error-free grant proposals and reports</li>
            <li><strong>Audit Readiness</strong> - Clear, professional transaction descriptions</li>
            <li><strong>Time Savings</strong> - Catch errors as you type, not during review</li>
            <li><strong>Accessibility</strong> - Helps users with dyslexia or spelling difficulties</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div class="help-tip">
        <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i>
        <strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Add organization-specific terms (equipment names, program names, vendor names) 
        to your dictionary for even faster data entry!
    </div>
    
    <div class="help-block">
        <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
        
        <h3>Spell check not working?</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Check Settings ? Spell Check ? ensure "Enable spell checking" is ON</li>
            <li>Refresh the page (F5)</li>
            <li>Try a different browser if issues persist</li>
        </ol>
        
        <h3>Too many false positives?</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Add common terms to your browser's dictionary</li>
            <li>Check if custom dictionary includes the term</li>
            <li>Consider if the spelling is actually correct</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3>Want to turn it off temporarily?</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Go to Settings ? Spell Check</li>
            <li>Uncheck "Enable spell checking"</li>
            <li>Click Save</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
